	   <tr><td colspan=2>I love my bard but I will not solo him.  Can we solo? Yes, but kiting is so slow away to kill some thing.  Charm kiting is great but fear and chain kiting are problematic given most zones and time per kill. 15 minutes to kill a yellow mob is insane.  Kunark and Veliuos have the resist cranked also so stay in Anti. if you can.<br>(Charm kiting is charming a mob to attack another mob and switching back and forth until you can melee both)<br>(chain kiting is selo's chain song [slow effect on target] and Dot[damage over time])<br>(Fear kiting is Fear to make them run and just chase them around attacking)<br>(DOt kiting is twisting selo and 2 DOts and running around in a circle until you can melee it.<br><br><br> ON the note of weapons I still use a PGT(hugs pgt) its damage shield and str buff almost permanent now at 35(payed 150 for mine) and I use a Dragoon dirk or a pair of gnoll whips in groups proc stun at lvl 25)<br> yes there are many better weapons but by lvl 26 you are not a real tank you are a singing meat shield with low hp and soso AC.  I almost never use my weapons anymore hand to hand from 10 to 96 in lvls 26 to 31.<br> WE DONT DO DAMAGE WE PREVENT IT. Bards and a healer should be a must in a group to make it run smooth.  We charge up the healer's mana and prevent the mobs from hitting the tanks and nukers.  IF YOU CANT TWIST STOP PLAYING THIS CHAR.  1 song will not help a group much.  3 with thunder as my tanks cant be hit hard and the clerics don't have to heal as much.......<br>I can raise ac 50 resists 50 and str and or dex with twisting in melee at 35 using just songs under lvl 10.  <br>   When making a bard Char. put the point into Charisma.  at later lvls you are crowd control charming and mezing adds.  I made the  mistake of putting points into INT 95 not charisma and now have to carry a pack of charisma gear into the hills everytime to have a 131 charisma.  though this is great for skilling up and trade skills.  Int is only a factor for skilling and mana at lvl43 don't bother.  Wood elf is good for tanking with a high dex and half elf(me) is solid also.<br>  ON deities watch it I have Veeshen and was threathening from Brell(dwarfs).  Also look on this site for racial armors and their main deities for armors and weapons that followers can use most will be better than most twinkable items and can be traded to other classes later(wish I was a twink mister lvl2 blueberry) indigo blades are really fast and high elf weapons too.<br><br>Hope this helps,<br>Frostpipes Gypsyrover of Povar<br><br> <br>&nbsp;<br>I sing in offering to Veeshen and give %t to her</td></tr>
