<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99494626469484></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99494626469484><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=99494626469484>RE: Weapons</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jul 12th 9:57 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>if you're not a twink, and you're at least level 40, you need to get to skyshrine and try to pick up a full set of guardian armor. Theres also a guardian sword (9 24, 5 str, 5 dex, 3 to all saves - either melee). All of these items are no drop and are attainable at level 40 with a strong group. It takes time to get this armor, but I know level 57 melee in uber guilds who are still wearing pieces of it. The legs and the girdle both have 5 cha, and there are a ton of saves on the set. Its really good stuff for any hybrid class. <br>One thing to note is that obtaining a set of this armor will destroy your CoV and make you KoS in skyshrine, but on the upside the storm giants in Kael will like you (frost giants will still hate you though).<br>Its tough to get to this zone and can be a dangerous journey, so get bound at every point you can along the way and bring all the necessary maps - it can also be a pain waiting for some of the items to drop, but in the long run you'll be glad you spent the effort. Also of note is that every guardian piece (including the sword) is no drop/lore (except the bracers aren't lore) and many of the items that drop are left to rot by people who can't loot them. I got about half of my guardian looting stuff that other people didn't want.<br><br>Hope this helps out<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
